The paper describes the development of a visual-inertial odometry-aided autonomous drone, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of a visual sensor for navigation and control also suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of model predictive control (MPC) and multisensor fusion (MSF), which are topics in control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG) respectively. Finally, the paper offers open-source code and tutorial documentation, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and open-source software development.
